2B5010C3.Line7.EDC73: A god that demands flesh. That rewards its consumption.

5D72A43D.Line1.EDC73: For days, the scent has lingered. At first, it troubled me.

915B9741.Line5.EDC73: But there is a sweetness to it, and alongside the buzzing of flies I hear the croon of an older thing.

F7671DBF.Line3.EDC73: Rotting flesh, the smell and the sound of corpse-flies ever present.
